Did you know divers practice new dives out of the pool BEFORE we go and try it in the water?

Using a harness and trampoline is extremely helpful in getting a feel for a new dive before taking it up to the platform. Not every pool has access to this, but when it’s available it’s extremely helpful 🙌🏻

#diving #divetraining #trampoline #athletemotivation #gymtraining

5 years ago I risked it all to win 🥇

At my final NCAA Championship I switch my last dive to the hardest dive I knew at the time. Because of this change, my degree of difficulty went way up and gave me a chance to win gold…but I still had to do the dive well to win. I reset, stayed present and gave it my all…and I won my 5th and final NCAA Gold Medal 🥇 

College diving is fun. You can’t switch your dive like this at the Olympics. Doing this adds excitement to the event. Good luck to all of the divers competing at NCAA’s this week! 👏🏻

This is one of my favorite memories from my college career 😎

I hit my feet on the board in round one and was fighting with every dive just to end up on the podium. I knew I need a huge last dive to win the bronze medal, so I switched from a front 3 1/2 to a front 4 1/2 on the board. I ended up hitting the dive for a perfect score and this still is my highest scoring dive ever at 114 points 🤯 Don’t be afraid to take risks in the pursuit of greatness!

8 years of being in an out of the boot and the journey for health continues. 😪

Just wanted to let y’all know that I’ll be going in for my 5th foot surgery next week. It’s been a long road just to end up no better than I was before my 1st surgery, but I’m still fighting.

I’m sure I’ll write more words soon, but just know I’m doing okay. I’m tired, I’m in pain, but God is still good. Healing will come one of the these days.

For now, enjoy these flashbacks to some moments of me rocking the stylish boot over these past 8 years 😂
